nal string, potentially using an else statement with parser.add_option instead. I need to get the exact formatting right!**Considering argument detection**\n\nI need to figure out how to handle optional values in argument detection. For instance, with `--foo --bar`, if the parser knows `--bar`, it should see that `foo` takes an optional value, prompting for user input but leaving `--bar` as is. However, if `--bar` isn’t recognized, it might cause an error after the prompt. I guess I'm trying to clarify how to manage these cases effectively!","format":"openai-responses-v1","index":0},{"type":"reasoning.encrypted","data":"gAAAAABp_YZXbAr-ynRb-zpaYoAkjdbwD9V5GUqAEr9SeTKKQuJlocUKVFX9Fg47-seAUhdcXY_N9WoNWX1-hXGB78UUiFa7XSeScLVUnBO8lZqcGToLq7ABNlqmnFsmPzGiuSHmNP6CckUcxxYKR2oQ0MPlp69P-BfNj88gPfgfh_zRQLqrtcFCL3FDyyjnMm5lNwGT2KZ3M7OIXTvFqg--6JheRzpcTxr5qWCJvhpJ7M6NXqNmZeiNRZeuA7TBZb72uQHlna3X7VK87zWLhRKUtGwe_ki3qm2JJEB9vzuOwUpAkSLXPpaxBi5tAQSnYWU-uV1cEd5t1L6Rll3iLEtnB8lC7fNMMsPoPJJdg-_P9Itle-3TKfFDxjE9Q-3oyVUT8_S27efjYt8UxfQi8LtPrg2ASbpS-FRBCoZLn0hjqQargaEDiTf6_R4mB7b2F1rYveGB_NNcd73-M1jO7oCMBR6fZBhxXYuSH0PJqjpx3J_JWxiaqu_qNrN3257uli9nVp0wzfeg9xEg4V95ZGTobCo_4hSnjv0u1s_8g6QHX5I09IKfp_Vnh7XROmKOWdp0YbdIffnNDwy7EbIO4wgsYPlsRuUNbEGNs2q6VH7WKcwXbcrnFSw0Z-DWtKzzv8nMK3t8ZSQpNRx4Qe-PqdDhpgwBmS6hJ_yQHVoTWx5R07AfilHpW9ROXvisduKJ2o3gJM8WkfOmWFodAoY3PbiikkphQZZ3xoIhSWqmw8BFfk8jpN0gBenEkj5WrmoZaZEVBzvk7pmRTXgJxvYPEr91ZvfmN9IJyNXET4LXqlK2pGaK5aHYWQC0HIx7le4hK6X4BeHBe7WrKQMoBTDj3_7QKIUuIfB-lrHh9zMr2P_l_dhAArvBv1Lf9uQA36ftuUGJyqhNbK7AOvH9Oof5s1ihuyZr2JGIJn8SJn6WeKYNvc1S4KqmehDWJxrUmbFawed0Ptzo8YbzDMUIJEteTxE1WL0RTukKpS3lE9q4LrqWbqu05oG1KvSthYk2fBiakWAhS5Qn19Qt9SqV_nVGO01fgy4jUs5X0OInw7uMqfadEydPCTwt-YkBEdY8cUVYxWhZmgUDtgyzBYDyTJm3YyTqsBxJFEMzcGM4XuwqupaEwPv621BvKohp5FZnno8bMSYo_Le8XBnEGl7_LGm7nN6lcMCq0qgpg31oAgP13iNvJkXlAaF001a2Dj7wM4SsPPRuOQ8FMdrCT74ckYt_S7s0ZRgcrG0YAmhQgVy8ak32eRhcgOWuLQkrHrPzkW9y_bB8OaZx1jr2J-x3iqzYBRoAFT-2zl2Rp-ED-WrxetX0W4ftDy0re0Hw1t8CJU4fl33D5wXG3K_eWiqiTESM8lJomtql